  "prompt": "If a die is rolled, what is the probability that the number is greater than 4?",
  "response": "A standard die has 6 faces numbered from 1 to 6. The numbers that are greater than 4 on a die are 5 and 6. \n\nThere are 2 outcomes (5 and 6) that meet this condition. The total number of possible outcomes when rolling a die is 6.\n\nTo find the probability, we use the formula:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Probability} = \\frac{\\text{Number of favorable outcomes}}{\\text{Total number of outcomes}}\n\\]\n\nSo, the probability that the number rolled is greater than 4 is:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Probability} = \\frac{2}{6} = \\frac{1}{3}\n\\]\n\nThus, the probability that the number rolled is greater than 4 is \\(\\frac{1}{3}\\).",
